 {"id":"bd-cat-epic","title":"PORT: GNU catgets binary catalog parser to core::locale::catgets","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-04-25T02:28:01.944354Z","updated_at":"2026-04-25T02:33:12.510667Z","description":"Lift parse_catalog_bytes (~65 lines) and MessageCatalog struct + message_ptr lookup from frankenlibc-abi/src/locale_abi.rs into core::locale::catgets. Pure binary-format parsing \u2014 magic detection (LE/BE swap), header word reads, two-table layout, plane hash lookup. Format: 3-word header (magic + plane_size + plane_depth), 2 tables of plane_size*plane_depth*3 words each, then strings blob. Sub-bead 1: add the parser + lookup_message_offset(set_id, msg_id) -> Option<usize> (returning string-blob offset rather than raw pointer to keep core in #![deny(unsafe_code)]). Sub-bead 2: rewire abi to delegate.","closed_at":"2026-04-25T02:33:12.510667Z","close_reason":"Epic complete in 2 sub-beads. Net effect: ~140 lines of pure binary-format parsing in locale_abi.rs (parse_catalog_bytes + MessageCatalog + message_ptr + helpers + 4 const definitions) replaced by ~210 lines of pure-safe core::locale::catgets with 14 isolation-tested cases plus typed CatalogParseError. The catalog parser is now reachable from any caller and lives behind #![deny(unsafe_code)]. Side fix: pre-existing wchar_abi.rs let-Some-else syntax errors corrected."}
 {"id":"bd-cat-1","title":"PORT: catgets sub-bead 1 \u2014 core::locale::catgets module","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","epic":"bd-cat-epic","created_at":"2026-04-25T02:28:01.944354Z","updated_at":"2026-04-25T02:33:12.510667Z","description":"Add crates/frankenlibc-core/src/locale/catgets.rs with: CATGETS_MAGIC: u32 = 0x9604_08de; pub const CATALOG_HEADER_WORDS = 3; CATALOG_SLOT_WORDS = 3; pub enum CatalogParseError (InvalidMagic, TruncatedHeader, ZeroPlane, ArithmeticOverflow, TruncatedTable, MissingNul); pub struct MessageCatalog { plane_size, plane_depth, table: Box<[u32]>, strings: Box<[u8]> }; pub fn parse_catalog_bytes(bytes: Vec<u8>) -> Result<MessageCatalog, CatalogParseError>; impl MessageCatalog { pub fn message_offset(&self, set_id: i32, msg_id: i32) -> Option<usize>; pub fn message_bytes(&self, set_id: i32, msg_id: i32) -> Option<&[u8]> } where the latter returns the NUL-terminated message slice (without the NUL). Tests: synthesized minimal catalog (1 set, 1 msg), magic LE/BE detection, plane_size==0 / plane_depth==0 rejection, arithmetic overflow rejection, table truncation rejection, missing trailing NUL rejection, lookup hit/miss, hash-collision walk through plane_depth slots.","closed_at":"2026-04-25T02:33:12.510667Z","close_reason":"Added crates/frankenlibc-core/src/locale/catgets.rs with: pub const CATGETS_MAGIC=0x9604_08de, CATALOG_HEADER_WORDS=3, CATALOG_SLOT_WORDS=3; pub enum CatalogParseError (InvalidMagic, TruncatedHeader, ZeroPlane, ArithmeticOverflow, TruncatedTable, MissingNul); pub struct MessageCatalog { plane_size, plane_depth, table: Box<[u32]>, strings: Box<[u8]> }; pub fn parse_catalog_bytes(bytes) -> Result<MessageCatalog, CatalogParseError> with bidirectional magic detection (LE/BE), checked arithmetic for plane footprint, table chunks_exact, NUL-termination check on max-offset string; impl MessageCatalog { pub fn message_offset(set_id, msg_id) -> Option<usize>; pub fn message_bytes(set_id, msg_id) -> Option<&[u8]> }. 14 unit tests cover minimal catalog round-trip, magic LE+BE detection, header truncation, plane_size==0, plane_depth==0, plane overflow rejection, buffer truncation, header-only buffer, missing-message lookup, negative msg_id rejection, hash collision walk through plane_depth slots, message_offset blob-index returns valid range, message_bytes excludes NUL, slot offset past blob rejected."}
 {"id":"bd-cat-2","title":"PORT: catgets sub-bead 2 \u2014 rewire abi catgets shims","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","epic":"bd-cat-epic","created_at":"2026-04-25T02:28:01.944354Z","updated_at":"2026-04-25T02:33:12.510667Z","description":"Drop parse_catalog_bytes + MessageCatalog struct + message_ptr method from locale_abi.rs. catopen / catgets / catclose now wrap core::locale::catgets::MessageCatalog (or a registry of it). The abi keeps the nl_catd descriptor allocator + global Mutex<CatalogRegistry> + the CString fallback synthesis for catalog NULL-pointer paths. Verify catgets/catopen abi tests pass.","closed_at":"2026-04-25T02:33:12.510667Z","close_reason":"Removed CATGETS_MAGIC / CATALOG_HEADER_WORDS / CATALOG_SLOT_WORDS / MessageCatalog struct + impl message_ptr / catalog_word / parse_catalog_bytes (~140 lines) from locale_abi.rs. catopen now calls a thin parse_catalog_bytes wrapper that maps CatalogParseError \u2192 libc::EINVAL preserving the existing errno semantics. catgets calls catalog.message_offset(set_id, msg_id) and constructs the *const c_char from the catalog strings blob at the boundary. CatalogRegistry / next_catalog_id / nl_catd descriptor allocator stay in abi where they have to be. Side-fix: corrected pre-existing let-Some-else syntax errors in wchar_abi.rs that the linter pass had introduced. Verified via rch with CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch_target_frankenlibc_cc_bd-cat-2: 173/173 abi lib + 50/50 locale_abi integration tests pass; cargo clippy -D warnings clean; cargo fmt --check clean."}
-{"id": "bd-cs-epic", "title": "PORT: crypt($N$salt$) prefix parser to core::crypt::salt", "status": "open", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "epic", "created_at": "2026-04-25T02:34:55.852460Z", "updated_at": "2026-04-25T02:34:55.852460Z", "description": "Lift parse_crypt_salt (~34 lines) out of unistd_abi.rs into core::crypt::salt. Pure byte-slice logic: detect optional rounds=NNNN parameter (clamped 1000..=999_999_999, default 5000), extract salt up to next $ or 16-byte cap, return (rounds, &salt). Used by both crypt_sha256 and crypt_sha512. Two clean sub-beads."}
-{"id":"bd-cs-1","title":"PORT: crypt-salt sub-bead 1 \u2014 core::crypt::salt module","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","epic":"bd-cs-epic","created_at":"2026-04-25T02:34:55.852460Z","updated_at":"2026-04-25T02:36:30Z","description":"Add crates/frankenlibc-core/src/crypt/mod.rs with: pub const DEFAULT_SHA_ROUNDS: u32 = 5000; pub const MIN_SHA_ROUNDS: u32 = 1000; pub const MAX_SHA_ROUNDS: u32 = 999_999_999; pub fn parse_crypt_salt(salt_bytes: &[u8], prefix_len: usize) -> (u32, &[u8]) following the SHA-crypt =NNNN$ wire format. Tests: simple $ with no rounds (defaults to 5000), explicit rounds=10000, rounds clamping (10 -> 1000, 1_000_000_000 -> 999_999_999), garbage rounds value falls back to 5000, salt longer than 16 truncated, salt with no trailing $ (consumed to end), empty salt, prefix_len=0 (no prefix consumed).","assignee":"cod-frankenlibc"}
-{"id": "bd-cs-2", "title": "PORT: crypt-salt sub-bead 2 \u2014 rewire abi callers", "status": "open", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "task", "epic": "bd-cs-epic", "created_at": "2026-04-25T02:34:55.852460Z", "updated_at": "2026-04-25T02:34:55.852460Z", "description": "Drop parse_crypt_salt from unistd_abi.rs. crypt_sha256 and crypt_sha512 call frankenlibc_core::crypt::salt::parse_crypt_salt directly (returning u32 rounds, cast to usize at call sites). Verify unistd_abi tests + any crypt-related conformance tests still pass."}
-{"id": "bd-cs-1", "title": "PORT: crypt-salt sub-bead 1 \u2014 core::crypt::salt module", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "task", "epic": "bd-cs-epic", "created_at": "2026-04-25T02:38:15.879523Z", "updated_at": "2026-04-25T02:38:15.879523Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-25T02:38:15.879523Z", "resolution": "Added crates/frankenlibc-core/src/crypt/{mod.rs, salt.rs} with: pub const DEFAULT_SHA_ROUNDS=5000, MIN_SHA_ROUNDS=1000, MAX_SHA_ROUNDS=999_999_999, MAX_SALT_LEN=16; parse_crypt_salt(salt_bytes, prefix_len) -> (u32, &[u8]) handling SHA-crypt $N$[rounds=NNNN$]salt$ wire format with bidirectional clamp, default-on-garbage rounds, salt truncation to 16 bytes. Defensive: prefix_len > buffer returns (DEFAULT, empty). 17 unit tests cover all edge cases plus a real-world SHA-512 line."}
-{"id": "bd-cs-2", "title": "PORT: crypt-salt sub-bead 2 \u2014 rewire abi callers", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "task", "epic": "bd-cs-epic", "created_at": "2026-04-25T02:38:15.879523Z", "updated_at": "2026-04-25T02:38:15.879523Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-25T02:38:15.879523Z", "resolution": "Replaced inline parse_crypt_salt (~34 lines) in unistd_abi.rs with a 5-line shim delegating to frankenlibc_core::crypt::salt::parse_crypt_salt. 173/173 abi lib tests pass; clippy + fmt clean. Verified via rch with CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch_target_frankenlibc_cc_bd-cs-2."}
